<item>
            <title>[LU-1471] parallel-scale-nfsv3/v4: FAIL: setup nfs failed!</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1471</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is a test script issue in setup-nfs.sh and only occurs on SLES11 NFS client:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Exporting Lustre filesystem...
Shutting down NFS daemon: [  OK  ]
Shutting down NFS mountd: [  OK  ]
Shutting down NFS quotas: [  OK  ]
Starting NFS services:  [  OK  ]
Starting NFS quotas: [  OK  ]
Starting NFS mountd: [  OK  ]
Starting NFS daemon: [  OK  ]
client-15-ib: service: no such service rpcidmapd
client-1-ib: service: no such service rpcidmapd
 parallel-scale-nfsv3 : @@@@@@ FAIL: setup nfs failed!
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/28c65cbc-ae11-11e1-ae0d-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/28c65cbc-ae11-11e1-ae0d-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/295e0c42-ae11-11e1-ae0d-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/295e0c42-ae11-11e1-ae0d-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is no /etc/init.d/rpcidmapd file on SLES11 nfs-client package. All of the services are in /etc/init.d/nfs.&lt;br/&gt;
By only using /etc/init.d/nfs service, the NFS could be set and cleaned up successfully on SLES11 NFS clients.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>SLES11 NFS clients</environment>
